        "**5c)** Add a `hold_vote()` method that loops over `self.members`, calls `cast_vote(self.proposition)` on each, and appends each member's `.vote` to `self.votes`. Return the total number of \"yes\" votes (i.e. `sum(self.votes)`).\n",
        "\n",
        "**5d)** Add a `pass_law()` method. If the number of yes votes exceeds `max_members // 2`, return `\"{proposition} is now law!\"`, otherwise return `\"{proposition} was rejected.\"`.\n",
        "\n",
        "**5e)** Test your Parliament:\n",
        "- Create three parties with different policy preferences\n",
        "- Create 5 politicians belonging to various parties\n",
